                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "DgLzQ",
                  "name": "Pull Quote 1",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "padding": [
                    16,
                    40
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "hsyHc",
                      "fill": "#111e5c",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "“I would very much like to see the findings of the first investigation to be shared prior to the opening of a new investigation. So I will not be supporting this motion.”",
                      "lineHeight": 1.35,
                      "fontFamily": "Playfair Display",
                      "fontSize": 26,
                      "fontWeight": "normal",
                      "fontStyle": "italic"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "YYfYV",
                      "fill": "#6b7280",
                      "content": "— Councilmember Michael Griffith",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "600",
                      "letterSpacing": 1
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "GpaL2",
                  "fill": "#374151",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "City attorney Mark Hoffman recommended authorizing the second investigation, telling council that releasing the first investigation's findings now “could have the effect of impacting the overall process,” and that handling both probes together would be “the better approach” from a due-process perspective. Mayor Lauren Simpson said she would follow that legal advice and voted yes.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "EQ8jl",
              "name": "divider1",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 1,
              "fill": "#e5e7eb",
              "justifyContent": "center"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "y3uOv",
              "name": "Workshop Section",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 18,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "mClp8",
                  "fill": "#3b5bdb",
                  "content": "WORKSHOP · SOLID WASTE & COMPOSTING",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 2
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "RjvTb",
                  "fill": "#111827",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "A fight over composting — and what the recycling refund could buy",
                  "lineHeight": 1.2,
                  "fontFamily": "Playfair Display",
                  "fontSize": 30,
                  "fontWeight": "700"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "FkTF5",
                  "fill": "#374151",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Council reached easy informal consensus on three of the four directions staff brought forward: pass through Republic's contracted increases, raise the city program fee a nickel (from $1.69 to $1.74), and keep the $1.06 enterprise fee in place to comply with reserve policy. The disagreement was over composting.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "myB75",
                  "name": "Options at a glance",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "#f8f5ed",
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": {
                      "top": 2,
                      "bottom": 2
                    },
                    "fill": "#111e5c"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "padding": [
                    24,
                    28
                  ],
