                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "In the near term, a Scraps-managed compost drop-off bin (or two) on city property — drop yours off, no curbside pickup. Composting then goes into the next hauler RFP as a bid alternate, with curbside service starting only when the new contract takes effect July 1, 2028.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "ufhIQ",
                      "name": "opt4",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "layout": "vertical",
                      "gap": 8,
                      "padding": [
                        16,
                        0,
                        0,
                        0
                      ],
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "O2gOT",
                          "name": "opt4Top",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "gap": 16,
                          "justifyContent": "space_between",
                          "alignItems": "center",
                          "children": [
                            {
                              "type": "frame",
                              "id": "v33ZL",
                              "name": "opt4L",
                              "gap": 12,
                              "alignItems": "center",
                              "children": [
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "DFRdn",
                                  "fill": "#3b5bdb",
                                  "content": "OPTION 4",
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 11,
                                  "fontWeight": "700",
                                  "letterSpacing": 2
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "AYrRj",
                                  "fill": "#111827",
                                  "content": "No action",
                                  "fontFamily": "Playfair Display",
                                  "fontSize": 18,
                                  "fontWeight": "700"
                                }
                              ]
                            },
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "N91rO3",
                              "fill": "#16a34a",
                              "content": "Saves $5–7 / mo",
                              "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                              "fontSize": 14,
                              "fontWeight": "600"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "vYsiD",
                          "fill": "#374151",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Drop the question, do nothing. Customers see only the EPR recycling credit on their bills — a $5–7 monthly savings — and rely on existing private services (Compost Colorado, Scraps) at $15–25/mo if they want curbside organics. Griffith pointed out this savings was missing from staff's slide.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "riL8a",
                  "fill": "#374151",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Staff's case for the slow lane: the team is already stretched thin by the drought response and an in-flight billing-system rollout. Dropping the recycling credit on customer bills only to chase it with a new composting charge a few months later, they argued, is a recipe for confusion. \"It's the community trust aspect of this we're really concerned about,\" deputy city manager Cindy Scheck told council.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "gYhkx",
                  "fill": "#374151",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Mayor Pro Tem Randy Moorman countered that the timing is exactly the point. According to Republic's own representative, the EPR refund is large enough to fund curbside organics with no net change to customer bills — at least at today's cost estimates. \"Arvada would have the lowest rate with a three-cart program in the entire state of Colorado,\" Republic's Steve Gilmore told council. The longer composting waits, the smaller that arbitrage gets.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "pJ86a",
                  "name": "Pull Quote 2",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "padding": [
                    16,
                    40
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "iGHII",
                      "fill": "#111e5c",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "“This is a rare opportunity for government to provide the same service for a lower cost to our residents — and we just don't get that opportunity very often.”",
                      "lineHeight": 1.35,
                      "fontFamily": "Playfair Display",
                      "fontSize": 26,
                      "fontWeight": "normal",
                      "fontStyle": "italic"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "lLh1j",
                      "fill": "#6b7280",
                      "content": "— Councilmember Michael Griffith, on the missing line item from staff's slide",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "600",
                      "letterSpacing": 1
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "HN5TK",
                  "fill": "#374151",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Councilmember Shawna Ambrose backed Moorman, framing curbside organics as wildfire defense (\"you are only as safe as your neighbor\") and equity. Mayor Simpson and Councilmember Lovisone sided with staff on the stepwise approach, but Simpson floated spring 2027 as a faster target than the 2028 RFP timeline — and asked staff to come back with a hybrid plan.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "neSr8",
                  "fill": "#374151",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Where this lands: by spring or summer, expect a city-property drop-off site managed by Scraps; by 2028, the next hauler contract will likely include curbside organics as a paid line item. The EPR recycling refund itself starts hitting customer bills this fall.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "rVfJy",
              "name": "divider2",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 1,
              "fill": "#e5e7eb"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "rs8IM",
              "name": "Whip Count",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 14,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "oujAk",
                  "fill": "#3b5bdb",
                  "content": "MEMBER PREFERENCES · NOT A VOTE",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 2
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "ri1hM",
                  "fill": "#111827",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Where each councilmember leaned — in their own words",
                  "lineHeight": 1.2,
                  "fontFamily": "Playfair Display",
                  "fontSize": 28,
                  "fontWeight": "700"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "JFtDd",
                  "fill": "#6b7280",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "No vote was taken tonight. Workshops are for examining a topic, not deciding it. Below is each member's preferred direction across the four composting options staff brought forward, plus a short quote summarizing why. A formal motion — at which point public comment is taken — would come at a future City Council Business Meeting.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.55,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
